New Features and Important Changes in ctools 1.0.0

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

18 December 2015


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes executable by executable the most important
changes made since the last release of ctools. The code complies to ctools
version 1.0.0 or above.


2. Configuration
-----------------
A special post processing of the Python module libraries has been added for
Mac OS X 10.11 and higher (El Capitan). This post processing is a replacement for
setting DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH during unit testing since the environment variable is
ignored in certain circumstances by El Capitan. Any errors that occur in the
post-processing will be ignored.


3. Python interface
-------------------
None


4. Support model
----------------
Adapt the ctool::create_ebounds() method to the change in the GEbounds
interface (the extname argument has been removed from the GEbounds::load()
method and replaced by using the GFilename class to handle extension names
as part of the file name).


